<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="prep-9-21">
  <title>Resources for 9/21</title>

  <objectives>
    <introduction>
      <p>For the content of this class, you will be expected to be able to do the following:</p>
    </introduction>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Recognize a <em>quadratic function</em> in both standard form and vertex form.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Given three points on the graph of a quadratic function, determine the system of equations necessary to find the formula for the quadratic function.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="video-activity-quadratic-equations-2">
    <title>Video &amp; Activities for Quadratic Equations</title>
    <p>
      Below is a YouTube video reviewing solving <em>quadratic equations</em>. It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.
    </p>

    <video youtube="IZzOgiYB4o4" />

    <example>
      <title>Quadratic Equations (Not on Quiz)</title>
      <p>
        The following problems are meant to be a review of solving quadratic equations.
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>x^2+4x+3=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>x^2+2x-15=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>3x^2+7x+2=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>4x^2-7x=2</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Suppose you are fencing in a rectangular region of area 100 square feet.  If the length is 21 feet longer than the width, find the dimensions of the fencing.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>2x^2+4x=13</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>3x^2+6x=-13</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              You stand on a ledge 10 ft above the ground and throw a ball up in the air.  The height of the ball at time <m>t</m> seconds is <m>h(t) = -16t^2+32t+10</m> feet. At what time does the ball hit the ground?
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </example>
    <p>
      Feel free to post any questions you have on the <url href="">FigJam board</url> for the next class.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="video-activity-intro-quadratic-functions">
    <title>Video &amp; Activities for Introduction to Quadratic Functions</title>
    <p>
      Below is a YouTube video introducing <em>quadratic functions</em>. It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.
    </p>

    <video youtube="IZzOgiYB4o4" />

    <example>
      <title>Introduction to Quadratic Functions</title>
      <p>
        Each of the following has three points from the graph of a quadratic function.  For each problem, do the following.
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              Determine if the graph opens up or down.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Guess how many <m>x</m>-intercepts the graph has.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Write the system of equations you would have to solve to write the quadratic function in the form <m>f(x) = ax^2+bx+c</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <image>
	            <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="quadratic-points-prep-1">
                <diagram dimensions="(300, 300)" margins="5">
                  <definition>f(x)=(-3/8)*(x-3)^2+(27/8)</definition>
                  <definition>g(x)=(3/16)*(x-6)^2+2.25</definition>
                  <definition></definition>
                  <coordinates bbox="(-1,-1,9,12)">
                    <axes xlabel="x" ylabel="y" hticks="(0,1,8)" vticks="(0,1,11)" />
                    <point p="(1,4)"> <m>(1,4)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(3,2)"> <m>(3,2)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(7,10)"> <m>(7,10)</m> </point>
                  </coordinates>
                </diagram>
              </prefigure>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <image>
            	<prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="quadratic-points-prep-2">
                <diagram dimensions="(300, 300)" margins="5">
                  <definition>f(x)=(-3/8)*(x-3)^2+(27/8)</definition>
                  <definition>g(x)=(3/16)*(x-6)^2+2.25</definition>
                  <definition></definition>
                  <coordinates bbox="(-5,-15,5,5)">
                    <axes xlabel="x" ylabel="y" hticks="(-5,1,5)" vticks="(-15,1,5)" />
                    <point p="(-3,-3)" alignment="sw"> <m>(-3,-3)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(-2,3)" alignment="nw"> <m>(-2,3)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(2,-13)"> <m>(2,-13)</m> </point>
                  </coordinates>
                </diagram>
              </prefigure>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <image>
            	<prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="quadratic-points-prep-3">
                <diagram dimensions="(300, 300)" margins="5">
                  <definition>f(x)=(-3/8)*(x-3)^2+(27/8)</definition>
                  <definition>g(x)=(3/16)*(x-6)^2+2.25</definition>
                  <definition></definition>
                  <coordinates bbox="(-1,-1,6,5)">
                    <axes xlabel="x" ylabel="y" hticks="(-5,1,5)" vticks="(-15,1,5)" />
                    <point p="(1,0)"> <m>(1,0)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(2,2)"> <m>(2,2)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(4,3)"> <m>(4,3)</m> </point>
                  </coordinates>
                </diagram>
              </prefigure>
            </image>
          </li>
          <li>
            <image>
            	<prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="quadratic-points-prep-4">
                <diagram dimensions="(300, 300)" margins="5">
                  <definition>f(x)=(-3/8)*(x-3)^2+(27/8)</definition>
                  <definition>g(x)=(3/16)*(x-6)^2+2.25</definition>
                  <definition></definition>
                  <coordinates bbox="(-1,-1,5,6)">
                    <axes xlabel="x" ylabel="y" hticks="(-1,1,5)" vticks="(-1,1,5)" />
                    <point p="(1,2)" alignment="s"> <m>(1,2)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(2,3)" alignment="s"> <m>(2,3)</m> </point>
                    <point p="(3,4)" alignment="s"> <m>(3,4)</m> </point>
                  </coordinates>
                </diagram>
              </prefigure>
            </image>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </example>
    <p>
      Feel free to post any questions you have on the <url href="">FigJam board</url> for the next class.
    </p>
  </subsection>

